<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="419" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,151,860]" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,333,800,824]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[837,922,800,824]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="419">lanceus</emphasis>
(= lanciform), referring to the shape of apical process of the aedeagus in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
